<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/837388-if-you-read-home-books-out-of-order-do">If you read HoME books out of order, do they still make sense?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_837388'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F7347.The_Book_of_Lost_Tales_Part_One">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/837388-if-you-read-home-books-out-of-order-do">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/837388-if-you-read-home-books-out-of-order-do">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/51646645-jeffrey"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1453134311i/51646645._UY100_CR25,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/51646645-jeffrey">Jeffrey</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">In some ways. You certainly can read them out of order, because each book is a collection of writings and not a single narrative. You will lose some o<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">In some ways. You certainly can read them out of order, because each book is a collection of writings and not a single narrative. You will lose some of the references if you read later books first, as the order of books is more to do with the chronological order of J. R. R. Tolkien's writing.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link418568" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=418568&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F837388-if-you-read-home-books-out-of-order-do%2Fanswers%2F418568-in-some-ways-you">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
