        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2189979634" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11398534418683963232">Ever since I started reading J.R.R. Tolkiens books this month I had this strong urge to read the short stories and learn more about the &quot;middle-earth.&quot; Now, I haven&apos;t officially read all of his books or the different series he has written that are set in the middle-earth but I still found these stories highly entertaining. I really liked how Christopher took his dads work and made it into the book of lost tales. And now after reading these I&apos;m even more pumped to read the rest of J.R.R&apos;s books. </span>
  <span id="freeText11398534418683963232" style="display:none">Ever since I started reading J.R.R. Tolkiens books this month I had this strong urge to read the short stories and learn more about the "middle-earth." Now, I haven't officially read all of his books or the different series he has written that are set in the middle-earth but I still found these stories highly entertaining. I really liked how Christopher took his dads work and made it into the book of lost tales. And now after reading these I'm even more pumped to read the rest of J.R.R's books. I seriously can't wait and I'm definitely going to read the second part of these lost tales. I hope they get better!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="11398534418683963232" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
