    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_347358968" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/347358968" />
    <a title="Legolas Greenleaf" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9319388-legolas-greenleaf"><img alt="Legolas Greenleaf" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1339552902p2/9319388.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/347358968?book_show_action=true">Jun 12, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Legolas Greenleaf" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Legolas Greenleaf" href="/user/show/9319388-legolas-greenleaf">Legolas Greenleaf</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Tolkien fans</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer347358968" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12498597718507475921">If you wanted to know how things came about in Middle Earth and the Undying Lands, this is a wonderful book to have for informational reference. From tales about the chaining of Melko (&apos;Melko&apos; was the original name, but it seems few people know that - perhaps they didn&apos;t read the book ;) ), to the coming of the Eldar, and the awakening of Men, the stories in this book are essential to fully understand the beginnings of Tolkien&apos;s world. <br/></span>
  <span id="freeText12498597718507475921" style="display:none">If you wanted to know how things came about in Middle Earth and the Undying Lands, this is a wonderful book to have for informational reference. From tales about the chaining of Melko ('Melko' was the original name, but it seems few people know that - perhaps they didn't read the book ;) ), to the coming of the Eldar, and the awakening of Men, the stories in this book are essential to fully understand the beginnings of Tolkien's world. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12498597718507475921" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


